Caddo Program for Jose Maria, June 17, 1967.  
Caddo songs.  
Introduction by Scott Tonemah and narration by Melford Williams, "Who Was Jose Maria?" Includes a brief outline history of the Caddoes, including their forced migration (1500?) beginning from their original homes in Southern Arkansas, Southwest and Lower Louisiana and East Texas-then to Nacadoches, Texas (1836) around Trinity and Lower Red River-next (1846) to a reservation in Brazos, Texas-then Oklahoma (1859) to present day.
